model.environment.map

Class MapBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.environment.map.MapBuilder

  • public final class MapBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
    A class that enables the practical building of a map. It includes functions to create queues, checkpoints, and so on.
    Author:
    S.A.M. Janssen

      • queue

        public java.util.List<SimulationObject> queue(Position start,
                                              int numberOfLanes,
                                              double queueWidth,
                                              boolean addBlockingWall,
                                              double degreeRotation)
        Creates a queue with a specified number of lanes and width. A blocking wall (a large wall to prevent agents from moving past the queue) can be added as well. The rotation degree indicates the angle the queue is rotated around its started position.
        Parameters:
        start - The starting position.
        numberOfLanes - The number of lanes.
        queueWidth - The width of the queue.
        addBlockingWall - Flag to indicate if we want to add a blocking wall.
        degreeRotation - The degrees it is rotated (in deg.).
        Returns:
        A list of SimulationObjects that form the queue.

                                              double degreeRotation)
        Creates a queue with a specified number of lanes and width. A blocking wall (a large wall to prevent agents from moving past the queue) can be added as well. The rotation degree indicates the angle the queue is rotated around the origin position.
        Parameters:

        numberOfLanes - The number of lanes.
        queueWidth - The width of the queue.
        addBlockingWall - Flag to indicate if we want to add a blocking wall.

        degreeRotation - The degrees it is rotated (in deg.).
        Returns:
        A list of SimulationObjects that form the queue.
